This program is the starting and central point of all eDev to Excel interactive sessions. It can be called directly from anywhere you wish in an application.
Parameters: Step(pi): To optionally specify a starting Wizard point. Last Main Program Variable(pi): To optionally specify the last Main Program variable.
Basically it does: - Run Through a wizard sequence to set up and maintain the interface as required. - Verify that thing a re complete and valid. - Perform the data view export. - Present the end result to the user.

This online utility program can be accessed from an <Option> button during the above ‘Data View Details Selection’ and 'Document Path Selection' the steps above. It provides access to additional options controlling the export of the information.
Parameter: ISN(pi): Identification of the associated row in the 'DataView Options' table

This program handles the fourth and last step of a Wizard sequence before actually producing the end result. Specifying an interface document where the data view information will be written is necessary for the utility to store a result that will be opened and presented on the screen afterwards.
Paramenters: Task ID(pi): Task Id of current online process. Next Step(po): Next step to go to upon completion of this wizard step.

This program handles the third and most important step of a Wizard sequence that will lead to the implementation of a 'Data View to' interface. This when actual layout of the export is specified.
Paramenters: Task ID(pi): Task Id of current online process. First VariableIndex (pi): Where to range from in the Data View. Last VariableIndex (pi): Where to range to in the Data View. Next Step(po): Next step to go to upon completion of this wizard step.

This program handles the second step of a Wizard sequence that will lead to the implementation of a new 'Data View To' interface. It enables limiting the overall scope of Data View items to consider for the purpose of a particular interface.
The 'Write First/Last Values' batch task below also provides default options such as: - Export Type = HTML - Path defaults to <Task ID>.xls - Text Delimiter = , - Text Identifier = "
Paramenters: Task ID(pi): Task Id of current online process. First Variable of DataView (pi): Can be Last variable of Main Program. Last Variable of DataView (pi): Can be first variable of this utility (DATA VIEW TO). Next Step(po): Next step to go to upon completion of this wizard step.

This program handles the first step of a Wizard sequence that will lead to the implementation of a new 'Data View To' interface. It simply welcomes the user to the process and gives him an opportunity to cancel.
Paramenter: Next Step(po): Next step to go to upon completion of this wizard step(po)

Finds every occurence of a String in a file and replaces it with another String.
Parameters: File Path: File to which the sring substitution will be applied. Find String: String to be replaced within the file. Replace with: New string to replace Find string with. Success to Write Result(po): Returns 'True' if it succeeded to write the result.
Considerations: - Work for 'Ansi' file content Only. - If the file is already in use by another application, a message will be issued to this effect as it will not be able to overwrite the content at the end.
